@ethus3h we do support multipart uploads, just not chunked transfer encoding. The parts have to be uploaded in individual requests.

Have you tried using boto? It's been a while, but I've had good experiences with using it with IA-S3 in the past for multipart uploads. I'm happy to help you troubleshoot this. Feel free to email me if that's easier.

Out of curiosity, why are you interested in using multipart uploads with IA-S3? In the archive.org IA-S3, the only real benefit of using multipart uploads is for resuming very large uploads. No doubt a very good reason, but it doesn't have all the same benefits that multipart uploads have with Amazon's S3 just to be clear. It can actually make for a slower ingest, depending on the scenario.

curiously, I found a trick that make it works. I think the issue is about I use @app.delete helper and have no entry with OPTIONS method for my path.
The trick I used add just and handler for OPTIONS method for each path I use (I don't use OPTIONS explicitly so it works for me).
Here is the code:
```python
def manage_cors(app):
    def option_handler(request):
        from sanic.response import text
        return text('', status=200)

    routes = set([k for k, v in app.router.routes_all.items()])
    for route in routes:
        app.add_route(option_handler, route, methods=["OPTIONS"])
```
