Hey @stefanv! It's debatable where this belongs. Because it's so much more lightweight than the viewer, I am inclined to argue that it can stand on its own. It does "one thing well" (TM), and that thing is segmentation.

We don't have interactive code elsewhere but I would argue that that is more a historical accident than a policy to be enforced. But I might be wrong. ;)

@soupault Yes, shipping the simple version is tempting, and imho it's pretty much ready. However, even a simple version becomes an API contract that gets embroiled in deprecation cycles and so on when we want to extend it. So, I think it's better to wait to have a full release cycle to think through exactly where we want to take this.

