@gaow Two points here:

1. I think that DSC should not get into the business of modifying the shell environment. This is out of scope of DSC.

2. We want to avoid introducing anything system-dependent within the `.dsc` file. For example, if I want to share my DSC experiment with Matthew, then my `.dsc` file should not contain instructions that will only work on my computer, and not Matthew's (consider that Matthew's python may be set up differently from mine).

