@soumith I was hoping for the networks in the modelzoo to be consistent initially. The fact that one needs to constantly look up model definition code to understand how to go about updating specific layers and then writing the kind of hacky code that I wrote above to actually update the layers is a major pain point. 

I understand that creating the `Sequential` models in the constructor makes sense since one should be able to leverage parallelism right out of the box. It would be super nice if `nn.Sequential` implemented the `__getitem__` method as it would allow us to index `Sequential` like an array and update layers accordingly. I don't know if you already have this in the works or how much effort it would be, but I would be willing to put in time for this feature.

One suggestion would be to allow for optional ID arguments to layers and have network weights load according to the specified ID, similar to how Caffe does it. Currently, if I call `VGG(pretrained=True, num_classes=200)` I get an error due to the network weights being inconsistent with the definition. This can be easily avoided by modifying the ID value after checking if the `num_classes` parameter is 1000 or something else.

@NBajanca, yes, I would accept a PR with that change. BTW, the `UserMixin` has an [access_token_expired()](https://github.com/python-social-auth/social-core/blob/9fb7a06a0618aa88d62b980392f77b5a5f91f98f/social_core/storage.py#L94) method that can make this code simpler to implement, something like this should do the trick:

```python
def get_access_token(self, strategy):
  if self.access_token_expired():
    self.refresh_token(strategy)
  return self.access_token
```

